intro: Schefflera urdanetensis, commonly known as the Urdanet schefflera, is a species of flowering plant in the family Araliaceae. It is native to the tropical regions of South America, particularly Venezuela. The plant is characterized by its dense, umbrella-like arrangement of leaves, which gives it a distinctive appearance. It produces small, greenish-white flowers that are typically clustered in umbels. Schefflera urdanetensis is often cultivated as an ornamental plant due to its attractive foliage and relatively low maintenance requirements.
